http://news.google.com/news/url?sa=T&ct=us/5-4&fd=R&url=http://www.marketwatch.com/news/story/glaxosmithkline-get-only-standard-fda/story.aspx%3Fguid%3D%257B88751189-38FC-48F8-9584-A02D9A4B9DB5%257D&cid=1116556836&ei=kP1eRvyYBIvO0AGtg6nSDQ GlaxoSmithKline to get only standard FDA review for Cervarix - MarketWatch Mutual Funds & ETFs GlaxoSmithKline to get only standard FDA review for Cervarix Last Update: 5:23 AM ET May 31, 2007 LONDON (MarketWatch) -- GlaxoSmithKline PLC said Thursday the U.S. Food and Drug Administration, or FDA, has declined to grant 'priority review' to its experimental cancer vaccine Cervarix. A priority review by the U.S. regulator, granted to medicines that represent a significant improvement compared with existing therapies, would have accelerated the approval and marketing of the vaccine in the key U.S. market. Instead, the drug will go through a standard 10-month review, and the company expects to get it to market in the U.S. sometime in 2008. GlaxoSmithKline applied in March for U.S. marketing approval of Cervarix, which targets cervical cancer and is expected to become a multibillion dollar product. It expects to launch the vaccine in Europe and several other markets in the second half of 2007. Earlier this month, it was approved by health regulators in Australia. At 0825 GMT, GlaxoSmithKline shares were down 16 pence, or 1.2%, at 1,312 pence in a broadly higher London market. The shares jumped Wednesday as the pharmaceutical company sought to defend its top-selling diabetes drug Avandia, the safety of which was questioned last week in a New England Journal of Medicine article. In a letter to U.K. medical journal The Lancet, GlaxoSmithKline's Chief Medical Officer Ronald Krall said that Avandia's side effects were comparable to those seen with two other widely used diabetes medicines, metformin and sulfonylurea. The critical report in the New England Journal of Medicine had triggered a slide in GlaxoSmithKline shares, sending them to their lowest level since April 2005 early in Wednesday's session. Company Web site: http://www.gsk.com Related Blog Posts & Articles U.S. stocks rise amid deal news Wachovia buying A.G. Edwards for $6.8 billion U.S. mortgage rates edge higher for third straight week U.S. GDP revised lower to 0.6% in first quarter Dell seen posting 22% drop in profit as it fights H-P threat Sign up to receive the Weekend TV Show Preview Wachovia buying A.G. Edwards for $6.8 billion Jobs wants to use iPhone to put the 'baby Internet' to bed U.S. stocks rise amid deal news Want to beat the market? Take the inside path U.S. futures up after Wachovia deal, Yahoo upgrade Thursday's biggest stock gainers and decliners U.S. GDP revised lower to 0.6% in first quarter Stocks in focus for Thursday Dell seen posting 22% drop in profit as it fights H-P threat Rouleau still seeing a 'mini-bull' market to be avoided Wachovia buying A.G. Edwards for $6.8 billion Jobs wants to use iPhone to put the 'baby Internet' to bed Big drug wholesalers may get bigger, with FDA help Five ways unmarried partners can safeguard their finances Three specialty REITs to buy on a pullback Growing share of 'Big Three' drug wholesalers gets attention Want to beat the market? Take the inside path U.S. GDP revised lower to 0.6% in first quarter U.S. mortgage rates edge higher for third straight week Bristol-Myers pleads guilty in federal Plavix case U.S. stocks rise amid deal news Wachovia buying A.G. Edwards for $6.8 billion U.S. mortgage rates edge higher for third straight week U.S. GDP revised lower to 0.6% in first quarter Dell seen posting 22% drop in profit as it fights H-P threat Get the Latest MarketWatch News >> Company: GlaxoSmithKline plc (GSK) Dow Jones Licensing Services Dow Jones Online Network: Copyright &copy; 2007 MarketWatch, Inc. All rights reserved. By using this site, you agree to the GlaxoSmithKline to get only standard FDA review for Cervarix - MarketWatch Intraday data provided by , a division of Int