http://news.google.com/news/url?sa=T&ct=us/6i-0&fd=R&url=http://www.dogflu.ca/05302007/13/european_children_getting_fatter&cid=1116808849&ei=kP1eRvyYBIvO0AGtg6nSDQ European Children Getting Fatter | DogFlu.ca Ontario Animal Shelter Contact Information Health Information for Human Beings Human Conditions and Diseases European Children Getting Fatter According to a European top health official approximately 21 million children on the continent are either overweight or obese A new study finds that almost half of Europeans are either overweight or obese. "The numbers are frightening," said EU Health Commissioner Markos Kyprianou. According to Kyprianou, bad diets and lack of exercise, account for 6 of the 7 factors that lead to bad health. "Everybody has to be blamed â€” including the authorities, including the industry, including the consumers," he added. Kyprianou states that European kids are becoming more and more overweight, a fact that does not bode well for the future. "If we don't act, today's overweight children will be tomorrow's heart attack victims," he said. It is estimated that 21 million European children are either overweight or obese. "Even more worrying is that the rate of increase of that number is more than 400,000 children a year. Now the biggest problem of obesity is in the Southern member states who have abandoned the Mediterranean diet and go for same kind of nutrition of fast food as elsewhere," Kyprianou said. Being overweight or obese significantly increases one's risk of a number of diseases ranging from diabetes to heart disease, thus having a large percentage of children dealing with obesity is not a good indicator of the future. Click Here to Join the Discussion! at 2007-05-30 17:04 | Copyright Â© 2006 DogFlu.Ca All rights reserved.
