tudy Links Poor Sperm Quality to Cell Phone Use Male Infertility May Have Obesity Link Sperm Quality Declines As Men Age The test is 95 percent accurate compared to standard lab tests, but even more important, it stresses that it takes two to make a baby. "Many women believe that the ability to conceive a baby is primarily up to them," Robert Thompson, president of Genosis said in a news release. "In fact, research shows that the issues affecting fertility are almost evenly split between the sexes. Because of this it is essential to involve and screen both partners." Fertell retails for approximately $100 and is available at CVS/pharmacy and Longs Drugs Stores, and also online at See Next Story in Health Vignette StoryServer 5.0 Mon Jun 04 17:10:42 2007 Vignette StoryServer 5.0 Mon Jun 04 16:46:30 2007 Decisions that can change your child’s life Latest Fox News Headlines People having sex in their sleep Golf swing and your health Coffee and gout link 'Living Corpse' Wakes After 19-Year Coma John Ramsey and Beth Holloway Twitty Are Dating Condemned Texas Inmate Wants to Leave 'Em Laughing Feds Hoped to Snag Bin Laden Nuke Expert in JFK Bomb Plot 3 Illinois Teens Arrested After Massive Food Fight Bloodbath on 'The Sopranos' Paris Hilton Completes First Night in Jail Komodo Dragon Mauls, Kills Boy, 8, in Indonesia Officer Details Hair-Raising Encounter With Missing Woman’s Husband Amsterdam's Ladies Pose Nude on Bicycles for American Photographer Spencer Tunick Arkansas Town Without Police Force After Officer Is Fired Larry Flynt: $1 Million for Proof of Sexual Encounter With High-Ranking Government Official Iranian Minister Calls for Temporary Marriages to Fulfill Sexual Desires Democratic Candidates Debate Terror, Iraq Jilted Cop Killed After Shooting Former Flame Terror Group Claims U.S. Soldiers Captured in Iraq Were Killed Studies Claim Women Don't Care About Penis Length Study: 'Sexsomnia' Causes People to Have Sex in Their Sleep Iranian Minister Calls for Tempor